{
  "stem": "12768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 17.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "And I-- it was her, Kate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "Hofgorn ?] was her name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "Later, she married a friend of mine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "And I-- I asked her if she knew where my mother was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "She said, I think she is on the other train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then I had no more reason to-- to stay there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw the Rabbi Friediger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had also been interned, because he never believe that the Germans would come to the house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so at the Seder one night, they came and just knocked on the door.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he went and opened the door, and they just left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I mean, they took them, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So then I had no other reason to stay, that I knew that they were free now.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I went back to camp the same day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I went to the captain and I thanked him for letting me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he said, I want you to be in charge of all ammunition.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there will be a column of trucks, you know, and you will ride front gun on the truck, you know, and I said, whatever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we went to the southern part of Sweden and were lying there in camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were lying in tents.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we slept-- I think there was 24 in each tent, you know, and had like a little stove in the middle, which didn't do nothing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So for two weeks we were lying there freezing our rear ends off.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And unfortunately, the Germans in Germany capitulated to the British on the 4th of May at 8 o'clock at night.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nobody knew it in Denmark till the 5th of May.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And on the 5th of May, we were moving to the harbor in Elsinore, and we sailed across to Denmark.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
